snippet.textDisplay:
I am Australian. Yet I have called New Zealand home for 6 years, and showcase this truly special country every day as a tour guide.

I pay homage to Eugene Bareman, and what he's achieved at City Kickboxing. I LOVE how he has put not only little ol' NZ on the MMA map (TOTAL shoe-in for Gym of the Year), but ALSO Australasia as a whole. (Izzy was right; the crowd record stands BECAUSE it was Rob vs Izzy, "Oz vs NZ": {even though Whittaker was born in NZ, and Adesanya in Nigeria; go figure - you can't script this shit!!}).

BUT......

It was Max...

It is my opinion that Max Holloway is THE classiest dude in the sport. He is real. He is passionate. He's not just earning a paycheck; he's doing what Dana has worked two decades to try to achieve; he is TRULY making the spectacular sport of MMA legitimate.

In the past, I've NEVER backed an American against an Aussie. I've never backed ANYONE against an "Australasian" (Oz or Kiwi)!

But I was still disappointed with this outcome, Volkanovksi earns the belt. And I really docelebrate his success, but am still subdued. Because Max is THE Man!!

(And - as a side note - he's Polynesian, like my Maori brothers and sisters).

Joe Rogan says Max is the "consensus greatest featherweight of all time". Well, that can definitely be called into question.

Jose Aldo, with his decade-long unbeaten streak is most CERTAINLY in that conversation (although it IS only a two-horse conversation).

And it must be noted that Joe's own sentimentality, his ability to generate interest, must be taken into account;

And yet I too feel that Max's heart, honesty, and even fanboy approach to his own sport is a HUGE factor!

And so I, for one, DO NOT BLAME Joe!

I too DO agree that Max is the greatest Featherweight of all time.

I can analytically look at Aldo's run (by the way, he DID beat Moraes, and may he enjoy a rejuvenated love of the sport and run of success at Bantamweight, and once a couple of lads have their shot at Triple C I would absolutely LOVE to see Aldo rip in), I personally concur with Joe's assessment that Max is the greatest Featherweight because of, well, EVERYTHING he brings and represents.

Max Holloway, you are the MAN!!!!

Classy in victory, defeat, and just LIFE in general.

And - ONE DAY - (maybe as a charity match), I'd throw my money at seeing you versus the SECOND classiest dude in the sport, DC, for the true title of "DADDEST MAN ON THE PLANET"!!!!

Kia Kaha!!
